task.summary: Added ability to hide and reveal tables accordingly; For example, only the servers table will show up initially. If you click on one of the servers, only the servers and queue table for that server will show up. If you click on a row in the queue table, you will see the redis set on the redis table.
Made nested table reveal function work and figured we could use a hidden input html value to keep track of the server that is clicked on.
Added basic JUnit tests for Redis-client class. Will need to find out how to get cachekeys to key names.
Fixed jsp to have more efficient way to get queue into array from redis server. Also fixed test cases.
